{"questionId":"4022","questionHtml":"<p>Two wires, X and Y, are made from the same metal. The wires are connected in series.&nbsp;The radius of X is twice that of Y. The carrier drift speed in X is <em>v</em><sub>X</sub>&nbsp;and in Y it is <em>v</em><sub>Y</sub>.</p>\n<p><br>What is the value of the ratio <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{{\\text{v}}_{\\text{X}}}}}{{{{\\text{v}}_{\\text{Y}}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>v</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>X</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>v</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>Y</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>?</p>\n<p>A. 0.25</p>\n<p>B. 0.50</p>\n<p>C. 2.00</p>\n<p>D. 4.00</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"4022","referenceCode":"17N.1.HL.TZ0.15","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two wires, X and Y, are made from the same metal. The wires are connected in series. The radius of X is twice that of Y. The carrier drift speed in X is vX and in Y it is vY. What ","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"15","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.1 – Electric fields","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}